From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LTV Corp.: The steel and aircraft-technology firm reported a $30.4-million net 
loss for the third quarter, contrasted with net income of $85.7 million a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
The Dallas-based firm cited "a significant decline in operating results and 
lower interest earnings" for the loss. The 1989 quarter included $42 million in 
income from an investment in a stainless steel-producing company, as well as 
higher interest income. Sales declined 4% to $1.45 billion. 
</P>
