<TEXT>
<P>
Manville Corp.: The international manufacturing and natural resources company 
posted third-quarter earnings of $24.5 million, down 39% from a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Sales totaled $576 million, a gain of 5%. The Denver firm attributed the 
results in part to its acquisition of Visypack Pty. Ltd., a leading producer of 
lithographic folding cartons in Australia. The company also noted an expense of 
$4.8 million for professional fees because of the restructuring of funding for 
the Manville Personal Injury Settlement Trust. 
</P>
