</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 5; Column 2; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
82 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
R. H. Macy &amp; Co.: The owner of Bullock's and I. Magnin, along with its 
namesake Macy's stores, saw its losses quadruple in the fiscal year ended July 
28. 
</P>
<P>
The New York-based retailer posted a loss of $215.3 million for the 12 months. 
Sales rose 4.2% to $7.27 billion. In its fourth quarter, Macy's lost $79.9 
million on sales that climbed 2.6% to $1.63 billion. A year earlier, it lost 
$57.4 million. The company said its performance was hurt by the national 
slowdown in spending. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
