<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: VENTURA COUNTY SALES OF EXISTING HOUSES DROP 20% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sales of existing single-family houses in Ventura County slumped 20% in 
September from August and plunged 32% from September, 1989. The median price 
for houses sold in the county was $241,290 in September, up 3% from $234,006 in 
August, but 2% below the $245,450 median price a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The house-sales data was collected from the Camarillo, Conejo, Ojai Valley, 
Oxnard Harbor, Simi Valley and Ventura boards of Realtors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
