<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: SUPERIOR, TOPY FORM JOINT WHEEL-MAKING COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Superior Industries International Inc. in Van Nuys said it formed a joint 
venture company with Topy Industries Ltd. of Japan to sell cast aluminum wheels 
to Japanese customers. 
</P>
<P>
Superior is a major manufacturer of wheels and other auto accessories for U.S. 
auto makers, and Topy is Japan's largest wheel producer. Their new venture, 
Topy-Superior Ltd., is half-owned by each company and "is a key step in our 
international marketing efforts," Superior Chairman Louis L. Borick said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
Topy-Superior's wheels will be shipped to Japan and to Japanese auto makers 
operating in the United States, the companies said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
