</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MARKETING EFFORTS PUSH SEMCO'S PROFIT UP 53% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Semco Instruments Inc., a Valencia producer of sensors and controls for the 
aerospace industry, said its profit in the first nine months of 1990 jumped 53% 
from a year earlier on a 52% gain in sales. 
</P>
<P>
In the period ended Sept. 30, Semco's net income climbed to $325,051 from 
$212,493 a year earlier, while its sales rose to $4.51 million from $2.97 
million. Semco attributed the gains to stepped-up marketing efforts in recent 
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
