<TEXT>
<P>
Morning Becomes a Revolving Door: Public radio station KCRW-FM's acclaimed 
"Morning Becomes Eclectic" music show is undergoing yet another modification. 
</P>
<P>
The show's longtime host, Tom Schnabel, left the station earlier this month 
after 11 years to pursue a career with A&amp;M Records. Fellow KCRW staffer 
Brent Wilcox took over temporarily while the station searched for Schnabel's 
replacement. Now, the station has decided to audition a variety of hosts over 
the air, and Wilcox has gone back to his early show "Nightland." CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
