<TEXT>
<P>
Elvis in London: A British car registration plate spelling ELVIS is expected to 
fetch a price equivalent to that of a London family house at auction. 
Christie's auctioneers say the plate ELV 1S is likely to break the previous 
record of almost $350,000 paid for the plate 1A when it goes under the hammer 
in December. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
