<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREPARING FOR 'THE BIG ONE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The county and all 86 of its incorporated cities staged a daylong 
earthquake-response drill Monday, dubbed "Disaster Response '90." The exercise 
was staged to evaluate the county's ability to assess the damage from a quake 
in Willowbrook and communicate with the cities, said Richard B. Dixon, county 
chief administrative officer. Included among the tests were the response to a 
collision between a chemical tanker truck and a van; helicopter transport of 
victims, and emergency evacuation of residents within a hazardous materials 
zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
