would respond to a major earthquake. Among the drills was one in which members 
of a hazardous-materials team aided people overcome by acid fumes, above. ; 
Photo, Nurse Elgi Baldonado, wearing visor with cross, tends to students 
portraying quake victims at Lynn Pace School in Bellflower. ; Photo, 
Firefighters wash off people who were "contaminated" by hazardous chemicals. ; 
Photo, A mock victim is examined at a triage area at the Shell Oil refinery 
training center in Carson. KEN LUBAS &amp; LARRY DAVIS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
