<P>
FLAGS FINALLY FALL IN TROJANS' FAVOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USC was aided by two 15-yard penalties in its only touchdown drive against 
Arizona State Saturday in a 13-6 victory at Tempe, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
Usually, the Trojans are hurt by penalties. 
</P>
<P>
The Trojans, penalized 11 times for 92 yards against Arizona State, have been 
assessed 73.8 yards a game in penalties this season, making them the most 
penalized team, in terms of yardage, in the Pacific 10 Conference. 
</P>
<P>
USC also was the most penalized team in the conference last season, when it 
absorbed 82.2 yards a game in penalties. 
</P>
<P>
Tailback Mazio Royster is listed among the Pac-10 rushing leaders after running 
for 97 yards in 26 carries against Arizona State. His average of 89.2 yards 
ranks fourth in the conference. 
</P>
<P>
A starter in USC's last four games, Royster was not listed previously because 
he hadn't played in 75% of USC's games. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
