<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BOXING REFEREE NEARLY REACHES END OF HIS ROPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police had to intervene to save a boxing referee from being hanged by angry 
fans in the southern Yugoslav town of Titograd, a police spokesman said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Enraged by referee Miodrag Bozjak's deciding vote Sunday in the defeat of a 
local boxer, the fans stormed the ring and began dragging him out of the sports 
hall. 
</P>
<P>
A rope had been strung over a nearby tree branch when police, arriving by 
helicopter, saved the referee. 
</P>
<P>
Police detained four people but later released them. Local police quoted the 
four as saying they only wanted to frighten the referee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
