<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
MAYOR SMITH LEADS IN FUND RAISING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Incumbent Mayor Charles V. Smith has passed the $20,000 mark in campaign 
contributions, giving him $6,000 more than the two other mayoral candidates 
combined, mandatory political finance reports show. 
</P>
<P>
Smith leads the pack with $20,532 in contributions. 
</P>
<P>
He has spent $17,543 -- about three times as much as rival Frank G. Fry -- and 
has $1,961 remaining on hand. Fry has received $10,649 in contributions and has 
$7,327 on hand. Mayoral candidate Darryl DeGraw has received $3,448 in 
contributions, spent $2,440 and has $1,008 remaining, the reports show. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, City Council incumbent Anita Huseth has also pulled ahead in 
contributions received. After trailing council candidate Craig Schweisinger in 
September, she has raised $12,165; he has raised $8,536 in that period. 
Schweisinger has used up almost all of his contributions and has $170 on hand. 
And after spending $8,529, Huseth has $4,468 remaining. She has also received a 
new $4,000 loan from her husband, the documents show.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
