<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA POLICE CONTINUE HUNT FOR GUNMAN WHO KILLED 3 MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police today continued to search for the gunman who shot and killed three men 
and injured a fourth late Monday outside an apartment complex in a neighborhood 
beset by drug-related crime. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana police also released the names of the victims. 
</P>
<P>
Killed in the shooting were Angel Brito Guadarama, 16; Mario David Mora, 23, 
and Noel Hererra Arroyo, 20, all of Santa Ana, according to Lt. Robert Helton. 
</P>
<P>
Miguel Angel Toledo Soto, 22, of Santa Ana is at UCI Medical Center in Orange 
in serious condition with several bullet fragments still lodged in his head, a 
medical center spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said that although Soto's doctors describe him as 
"disoriented," he has shown signs of responding favorably to treatment. 
</P>
<P>
Helton said the gunman -- described as in his mid-20s and wearing dark clothing 
-- walked through the Fairview Villas apartment complex and opened fire on four 
men standing next to a bank of public telephones. Two of the victims fell to 
the ground and died immediately, while a third ran about 25 yards to an 
apartment, where he died. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect then fired two rounds through the front windshield of a passing 
car, with one of the rounds hitting Soto in the head. There was no indication 
that Soto, a passenger in the car, had any involvement with the other victims, 
Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
The fourth man at the telephones was uninjured, and police are searching for 
him. 
</P>
<P>
"There's no evidence that would indicate it's gang-related. None whatsoever," 
Helton said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
