<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAPRIATI RANKED 10TH IN WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIAMI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jennifer Capriati cracked the top 10 rankings in women's tennis by winning the 
Puerto Rico Open. 
</P>
<P>
Capriati, seeded second, defeated top-seeded Zina Garrison 5-7, 6-4, 6-2 on 
Sunday to take the $150,000 event, her first victory since turning pro in 
March. 
</P>
<P>
The victory boosted her to No. 10 in the world in the latest rankings. 
</P>
<P>
At 14 years, 6 months, 29 days, she became the third-youngest woman to win a 
tennis tournament. The youngest was Tracy Austin, who was 14 years, 1 month, 4 
days when she won at Portland in January, 1977. 
</P>
